comment.narrative:
1. Local Authorities inducted on the national devolution process 
2. Implementation of the Urban Service Level Benchmarking (SLB) Tools, including the Corporate Governance and Infrastructure monitored and tracked; 
3. Rural District Council (RDCs) SLB tools developed and tested for rolled out in the 60 Local Authorities;
4. Develop the Regional Gross Domestic Products (GDP) frameworks to guide the piloting Cluster Local Economic Development initiatives.

1. 2 The Government devolution agenda and guiding frameworks were reviewed by the Rural District Councils leadership at the RDCs Annual General Conference for rolling out in the local government sector; 
1.2 The draft provincial and district Gross Domestic Product (GDP) framework was developed for consideration by Government.
1.3 The 32 Urban Local Authorities were Peer Reviewed to assess the implementation progress of the SLB frameworks, including the Corporate Governance and Infrastructure benchmarks and indicators;
3.2 Coordination structures for the Rural Local District Councils (RDCs) Service Level Benchmarking (SLB) were setup, the priority benchmarks and indicators were identified, SLB tools were developed and tested in four RDCs (Mhondoro-Ngezi, Muromebdzi, Tongogora and Nkayi). The SLB framework will be rolled out in all 60 RDCs in 2020;

1. Support the Peer Review process for WASH (plus Non-WASH) Services Benchmarks in Local Authorities; 
2.Support the review of the Councils Induction Handbooks/Training Manuals and Training of Trainers (ToT);
3.Finalize the gender sensitive service delivery indicators framework into policy
